Defendant in custody.    
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 02-09-2018.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   That's one (1) year initial confinement, followed by three (3) extended supervision.   
Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Complete HSED/GED; 
2) Reimburse Manitowoc County $90.00 buy money;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) No contact with known drug users or dealers;  
5) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling at the agents discretion
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Pay costs of action during extended supervision;
The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration and Substance Abuse Programs.   
Defendant is entitled to 136 days time already served.   
Minutes.

State files an Amended Information charging Delivery of Schedule I, II or III Non Narcotics, contrary to Section 961.41(1)(b) a Class H felony.   
Guilty plea to the amended charge.   Convicted.  Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Complete HSED/GED;
2) Reimburse Manitowoc County $90.00 buy money;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Have no contact with any known drug users or dealers;
6) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
7) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
8) Pay costs of action; 
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) Ninety (90) days jail imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
11) Provide DNA sample.  
Court finds that defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment of record pursuant to Section 973.015 of the Wisconsin Statutes upon successful completion of sentence.
